{
  "doc_id": "33320",
  "text": "In order to do that, we implemented both our proposed attack and the attack presented in [CITATION_1] , using the IMDB sentiment classification dataset, instead-of the dataset used in section IV-A. We used 5,000 samples for training, 5,000 samples for validation and 5,000 samples for test. We used the first 80 words in each review, padding with zeros if the review was shorter. All sequences were one-hot encoded. We used the 20,000 most frequent words in the reviews. The classifier used is LSTM, with the same hyper-parameters as specified in section IV-B. For our attack, we used the same surrogate model type and hyper-parameters as in sections IV-B and IV-C.",
